what's the word about legal--

00:10:19.410 --> 00:10:20.490
not combative.

00:10:20.490 --> 00:10:21.500
Adversary.

00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:22.310
Yeah.

00:10:22.310 --> 00:10:23.930
And he actually put--

00:10:23.930 --> 00:10:26.013
that day after the
evaluations came out,

00:10:26.013 --> 00:10:28.490
he had entire PowerPoint
slide deck with quotes

00:10:28.490 --> 00:10:29.830
from the evaluation.

00:10:29.830 --> 00:10:31.985
And he basically would go
through and explain why--

00:10:31.985 --> 00:10:34.610
there would be criticisms like,
we should not be forced to take

00:10:34.610 --> 00:10:36.360
notes in this class
because it forces--

00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:38.526
which I think is absolutely
ridiculous for a student

00:10:38.526 --> 00:10:39.500
to say.

00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:42.067
And he would explain why I
think it's important for you

00:10:42.067 --> 00:10:42.650
to take notes.

00:10:42.650 --> 00:10:45.230
And he actually had-- as a
scientist he had evidence

00:10:45.230 --> 00:10:46.525
and he pulled out publications.

00:10:46.525 --> 00:10:48.950
He was like, students
learn 32% better

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:50.560
when they write
down things by hand

00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:52.220
rather than just seeing slides.

00:10:52.220 --> 00:10:54.080
He went through all
of these comments

00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:56.850
and basically defended
his decisions.

00:10:56.850 --> 00:11:00.437
And then the decisions
that he decided to change--

00:11:00.437 --> 00:11:02.270
for example, someone
