asking the alumni for feedback.

00:45:28.410 --> 00:45:33.770
And so, Signa, I know you are
a Harvard alumnus and so are

00:45:33.770 --> 00:45:37.190
there-- if you reflect back on
your undergraduate experience,

00:45:37.190 --> 00:45:39.900
are there things that-- are
there courses that you took

00:45:39.900 --> 00:45:40.650
that--

00:45:40.650 --> 00:45:44.240
or information you've
retained or skills

00:45:44.240 --> 00:45:46.390
you've retained from
your undergraduate years

00:45:46.390 --> 00:45:48.960
that you now realize like,
oh, I didn't appreciate

00:45:48.960 --> 00:45:53.820
that that same way when I was
going through it as I do now?

00:45:53.820 --> 00:45:55.650
Definitely.

00:45:55.650 --> 00:45:57.540
Actually, one of my
classes right now

00:45:57.540 --> 00:45:59.400
tends to be more
politically science focused

00:45:59.400 --> 00:46:03.450
and I was a social studies
undergrad major and had

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:06.390
