00:46:17.790 --> 00:46:19.950
me think back to
undergrad and thinking,

00:46:19.950 --> 00:46:25.190
wow, I wish I had paid more
attention in social studies 10.

00:46:25.190 --> 00:46:27.090
And it was just a
really good foundation

00:46:27.090 --> 00:46:30.780
for learning how to read
text and sort of pick up

00:46:30.780 --> 00:46:32.520
these ideas and
the main messages

00:46:32.520 --> 00:46:36.570
from the authors, which I
thought I knew how to do

00:46:36.570 --> 00:46:38.790
and then afterwards I was
like, no, actually now I

00:46:38.790 --> 00:46:41.730
know how to do this better.

00:46:41.730 --> 00:46:43.369
And looking back,
there are definitely

00:46:43.369 --> 00:46:45.660
classes that stick out that
I think I didn't appreciate

00:46:45.660 --> 00:46:48.525
at the time as much as I should
have and now very much value

00:46:48.525 --> 00:46:49.910
having done.

